SUMMARY:Longford Park and Reynold's Dog Park- route along canal
DESCRIPTION:Walking Tails\nThis week we will walk along the canal. The tra
 il in this direction is dirt and gravel. We will go out about 1.5 miles an
 d then come back the way we came\, for a total of 3 miles. CLICK DIRECTLY 
 ON THE MAP IF YOU THINK YOU ARE LOST. IT WILL BRING YOU RIGHT TO US WHERE 
 WE MEET.\n\nWe will be meeting near the dog park\, come early and let your
  dog play off leash in the dog park.\n\nStart Time: We will start hiking p
 romptly at the scheduled time.\n\nDuration of the walk – depends on the 
 people and dogs in the group. We frequently end up walking in smaller pack
 s based on the comfort level of the participants. In the past this walk ta
 kes about 1 hour or so.\n\nPlease remember pooh bags and that your dog mus
 t be on a leash that is no more than 10 feet long.\n\nFacilities: There ar
 e bathrooms at the dog park\n\nNOTICE: By attending this event you are agr
 eeing that YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY AT ALL TIMES. The hike 
 leader and other members cannot be held responsible for any damages\, acci
 dents\, or liabilities incurred while hiking with us.
